==English==
===Etymology===
It was believed that the moon (Roman: Luna) sent you mad.

===Noun===
'''lunacy''' (''plural'' '''lunacies''')

# (Of a person or group of people) the state of being [[mad]], [[insanity]].
# Something misguided.

